<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">This uses pyportmidi for now, but may use its own bindings at some point in the</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">latency</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">is the delay in milliseconds applied to timestamps to determine</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">latency</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">is zero, timestamps are ignored and all output is delivered</span>

If </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">latency</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">is greater than zero, output is delayed until the</span>
